
[1]bigotry

   BIG'OTRY, n. Obstinate or blind attachment to a particular creed, or to
   certain tenets; unreasonable zeal or warmth in favor of a party, sect
   or opinion; excessive prejudice.

   1. The practice or tenet of a bigot.
